      "actor": "user",
      "content": "# Focus: arch\n\nToday's date: May 26 2026\n\n## Task\nAnalyze this codebase architecture and directory structure.\n\n## Write these documents to .planning/codebase/:\n- ARCHITECTURE.md - Pattern, layers, data flow, abstractions, entry points\n- STRUCTURE.md - Directory layout, key locations, naming conventions\n\n## IMPORTANT:\n- Use May 26 2026 for all [YYYY-MM-DD] date placeholders in documents.\n- Scope: (full repo) — explore the entire codebase.\n- Explore thoroughly using Glob, Grep, and Bash tools.\n- Write documents directly using templates.\n- Return confirmation only with file paths and line counts.\n\n## Agent Skills to Load:\n- repomix-explorer (for codebase analysis)\n- deep-research (for architecture patterns)\n\n## Document Templates (follow these structures):\n\n### ARCHITECTURE.md Structure:\n```markdown\n# Architecture\n\n[Generated: 2026-05-26]\n\n## Overview\nHigh-level architecture summary.\n\n## Architecture Pattern\n- [e.g., Clean Architecture, Hexagonal, Layered]\n- Why this pattern was chosen\n\n## Layers\n### Domain Layer\n- Entities, use cases, domain services\n\n### Application Layer\n- Use cases, application services\n\n### Infrastructure Layer\n- External integrations, data access\n\n### Presentation Layer\n- APIs, UI components\n\n## Data Flow\nHow data moves through the system.\n\n## Key Abstractions\nCore abstractions and interfaces.\n\n## Entry Points\n- API endpoints\n- CLI commands\n- Webhooks\n\n## Component Diagram\nHigh-level component relationships.\n```\n\n### STRUCTURE.md Structure:\n```markdown\n# Directory Structure\n\n[Generated: 2026-05-26]\n\n## Overview\nRoot-level organization.\n\n## Directory Layout\n- **src/** - Source code\n  - `/tools` - Tools and utilities\n  - `/hooks` - Lifecycle hooks\n  - `/features` - Feature modules\n  \n- **.opencode/** - OpenCode primitives\n  - `/agents` - Agent definitions\n  - `/skills` - Skill packages\n  - `/commands` - Slash commands\n  \n- **.hivemind/** - Internal state\n  - `/state` - Runtime state\n  - `/planning` - Planning docs\n\n## Key Locations\n- Entry point files\n- Configuration files\n- Test files\n- Documentation\n\n## Naming Conventions\n- File naming\n- Directory naming\n- Variable naming\n- Function naming\n\n## File Organization Patterns\nHow files are grouped and organized.\n```\n\n## Success Criteria:\n- [ ] ARCHITECTURE.md created with >50 lines\n- [ ] STRUCTURE.md created with >50 lines\n- [ ] Documents include actual file paths with backticks\n- [ ] Clear architecture pattern identified\n\nReturn format:\n```\n## Mapping Complete\n\n**Focus:** arch\n**Documents written:**\n- `.planning/codebase/ARCHITECTURE.md` ({N} lines)\n- `.planning/codebase/STRUCTURE.md` ({N} lines)\n\nReady for orchestrator summary.\n```",
